        new BasicTaskDetailsUi(mSelectedTaskUri).show(this);
```

(Note: this comes out the #469 changeset)

These should be `androidTestImplemenation`:
```groovy
    androidTestCompile('com.android.support.test:runner:' + ANDROID_TEST_RUNNER_VERSION) {
        exclude group: 'com.android.support', module: 'support-annotations'
    }
    androidTestCompile('com.android.support.test:rules:' + ANDROID_TEST_RUNNER_VERSION) {
        exclude group: 'com.android.support', module: 'support-annotations'
    }
```

The current design of `EntityProcessor` has some flaws.

Here is an initial proposal of a better design:
```
public interface EntityProcessingStage<T>
{
    /** Inserts the given entity into the database and returns the new version */
    T inserted(SQLiteDatabase db, T entity, boolean isSyncAdapter);

    /** Updates the given entity with the new values and returns the resulting version */
    T updated(SQLiteDatabase db, T currentEntity, T newEntity, boolean isSyncAdapter};
 
    /** Deletes the given entity */
    void delete(SQLiteDatabase db, T entity, boolean isSyncAdapter);
}
```

The various stages would be daisy chained like this: 
```
new Validating(new Moving(new Relating(new FtsIndexing(new ExecutionStage())));
```
Each stage would have access to the current values and the new values as updated by the previous stage as well as the resulting entity after the entity has been committed by the final stage.

